07/12/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The National Committee on Prevention of Human Trafficking adopted its national plan for the period 2005-2008 on Monday (6 December).
The committee also approved the action plan for prevention of human trafficking in 2005.
In other news, protesters rallied in front of the Croatian Embassy in Skopje on Monday, demanding the provisional release of former Macedonian Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski.
He was arrested in Croatia for alleged involvement in the 2002 murders of seven immigrants.
(HINA, MIA - 06/12/04)
